{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7cc9b6e-78e1-49a8-8df6-d7f0c8b775e7","content":"Two things change when moving to xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. Instead, pass `--filter` directly to the test executable (or via `dotnet test --`). The property names differ:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName` | `FullyQualifiedName` (same) |\n| `Category` | `trait:Category` |\n| `&` (AND) | `&` (same) |\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` (contains) |\n\n**2. New filter expression:**\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP) — pass filter after --\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&trait:Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr if running the test executable directly (common with MTP):\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&trait:Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- `~` (contains) becomes `~=`\n- `Category=Smoke` becomes `trait:Category=Smoke` (traits are prefixed with `trait:`)\n- Filters go after `--` to pass them through to the MTP runner","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ea738934-d847-4617-a3f1-2a8fd896f034","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"9847:29E2AD:19232F:20F428:69FFD950"},"id":"7c69be0e-5827-4b0e-a708-9be7f25f6d76","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:03:21.331Z","parentId":"66a745a3-f3b4-4424-9785-8437a4974bbb"}
